## Layout Templates
When creating new applications or layouts, **always** follow the layout templates in `docs/agent/design/layouts.md`:
- **Marketing Layouts**: Use for public-facing websites, landing pages, and marketing content
- **Product/App Layouts**: Use for internal tools, dashboards, and application interfaces
  - Choose **dark horizontal navigation** for simpler apps (5-7 nav items)
  - Choose **dark sidebar navigation** for complex apps (hierarchical navigation)
- **Logo Placement**: Always include Equal Experts logo correctly placed:
  - Marketing: Full-color logo on light backgrounds
  - Product/App: White monochrome logo on dark navigation (Tech Blue)
- **Color Tokens**: Use sidebar color tokens (`bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar-foreground`, etc.) for dark navigation
- **Consistency**: All EE applications must follow these layout templates for brand consistency

## Component Development
- All components use Tailwind CSS v4
- CSS variables are defined in `@equal-experts/kuat-core/src/variables.css`
- Use Shadcn/ui MCP to discover component code
- Components should follow shadcn/ui patterns
- Always create a React and Vue component when asked to create a component
- Ask the user if there is a customised version of the component to use in Figma. If there is, use Figma MCP to understand it
- Use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- Components are installed via CLI: `npx shadcn@latest add [component]` (React) or `npx shadcn-vue@latest add [component]` (Vue)
- Always create supporting Storybook stories in apps/storybook-react and apps/storybook-vue

## Import Patterns
- React: `import { Component } from "@equal-experts/kuat-react"`
- Vue: `import { Component } from "@equal-experts/kuat-vue"`
- Core CSS: `import "@equal-experts/kuat-core/variables.css"`

## Build System
- Uses Turborepo for monorepo orchestration
- Uses pnpm workspaces
- Each package builds independently with Vite
- TypeScript is used throughout
- Agent docs are auto-copied to packages during build via `copy-docs` script

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS v4 with `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin
- CSS variables for theming (light/dark mode support)
- All design tokens centralized in `@equal-experts/kuat-core`
- Brand colors: EE Blue (#0066CC), Tech Blue, Transform Teal, Equal Ember
- Fonts: Lexend (sans), Lora (serif), JetBrains Mono (mono)
- Spacing: 8-point grid system (use multiples of 8px)
- Border radius: 0px default, 6px interactive, 4px inputs

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- Use path aliases: `@/*` maps to `./src/*`
- Follow existing component patterns
- Export components from package `index.ts` files

